latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Happy world dance day ! 

I really took my performing days for granted. I miss every bit of the journey to the show day. 

Long, tiring and fun rehearsals, water breaks that were used to gossip, learning, getting scolded and of course the finale. The show day. 

Backstage whispering, getting ready, the costume and the jewellery, helping each other get ready. On stage adjustment and whispering. Post show giggles about the mess ups and hoping our gurus didn’t notice (biggest delusion)! 

Praying that we get through covid safely and quickly so we can get back to doing the things we love! 

Shot this last year during the lockdown! 

Thankful to my gurus @rajaradhareddy @kaushalyareddy 💗
#worlddanceday #kuchipudi #dance #classical

latestPosts.caption:
One year ago, today.  I got my SOLO! 

26th October is and always will be one of the most cherished and life changing days for me, not only because I got my solo. Today, will always act as a reminder for me of how i pulled through the struggle regardless of all the uncontrollable obstacles that came in the way of me being released. And it was all me. My skill and hard work. No one had anything to do with this. 

I can’t go into depth but every time i had my solo check there was something or the other that came in the way. Sometime it was the weather, traffic, FADEC warning, change of runaway heading, etc. something was ALWAYS there. Imagine you’ve been told you’re getting your solo and as soon as you’re about to go for the landing the aircraft shows a warning. And my friend who went just right after me in the same aircraft, got solo released. 

Don’t get me wrong I was so so happy for him. But I started doubting my own capabilities and my flying. I resorted to the fact that im just not good. I was really demoralised. I felt horrible. 

But when it happened I couldn’t believe it happened because I had given up. 
My PIC (pilot in command) after landing went like POB (passenger on board) 01 and I turned around and was like 😦 “what? are you sure?”. He’s like “are you sure?”. First thing I did was scream when I was alone.

I don’t regret or resent the struggle I went through. I mean yeah it was bloody annoying and i wanted to break something every now or then. But it taught me and showed me a lot too. Grateful to fam and friends who supported me. It was worth it 🤍

And know your dad to record you crying and give you a taunt on how he got his solo before me :)

latestPosts.caption:
Maa Kamakhya •The Divine Feminine ⚜️

One of the most sacred of the 51 Shakti peeths ( the places where Maa Satis body parts fell on earth ) on Earth. Known as the goddess of desire and the giver of salvation. 

The only temple that celebrates annual mensuration of the goddess known as The Ambubachi Festival. Where the temple is shut for 7 days. 

As the part that fell here was the Yoni (female genital). You can even see the water flowing near the temple turning red. 

The energy of the temple radiates through your body. Just like the divine feminine energy - daunting but nurturing ♥️ 

#maakamakhya #kamakhya #assam #temple #india #shakti #shaktipeeth #guwahati

latestPosts.caption:
@dillidillwale , pickleball, rooftop court and good vibes 🎾 

Spent the day with these incredible athletes before the World Pickle ball league in Bombay, and the energy was electric! From a sportsman to sportsman it was inspiring to see their dedication and passion for the game. They definitely dominated the court and I can’t wait to see them in action again! 

Pickleball is definitely taking over, and I’m loving every bit of it! I never thought I’d go back to a racket sport, but pickle ball definitely nudged me in that direction! 

#dillidillwale #pickleballlife #leaguetime #worldpickleballleague
